key_facts:

summary:
- Feb 9, 2026: Assam CM Himanta Biswa Sarma reacts to Asaduddin Owaisi’s complaint over a now-deleted video depicting violence against Muslims, calling it genocidal hate speech; says he didn’t know about the video and will oppose Bangladeshi infiltrators; Owaisi files police complaint seeking action.

key_facts:
- Find Skills helps discover/install skills in open agent ecosystem
- Skills CLI is npx skills; key commands: find, add, check, update
- Workflow: identify need, search, present options, offer install
- Example install command and sample skill
- If none found, offer direct help or suggest npx skills init
- Metrics: weekly installs, repo, first seen, top installers
summary:
- The page introduces Find Skills, a tool to discover and install open agent skills.
- The Skills CLI (npx skills) is the package manager; key commands are find, add, check, update.
- Browse skills at skills.sh and install with npx skills add <owner/repo@skill>.
- When to use Find Skills: questions like how to do X, find a skill for X, extend capabilities, search tools/workflows, or domain help.
- How to help users: Step 1 identify domain/task; Step 2 search with npx skills find [query].
- Step 3 present options with name, purpose, install command, learn more; Step 4 offer to install with npx skills add <owner/repo@skill> -g -y.
- Example: vercel-react-best-practices provides React/Next.js performance guidelines; install with npx skills add vercel-labs/agent-skills@vercel-react-best-practices.
- Common categories: Web Development, Testing, DevOps, Documentation, Code Quality, Design, Productivity.
- If no skills found: acknowledge, offer direct help, and suggest npx skills init to create your own skill.
- Weekly installs: 164.2K; repo vercel-labs/skills; first seen 14 days ago; top installations include opencode, codex, gemini-cli, github-copilot.
notes: Accurate and comprehensive; a bit long but still within reasonable length. Includes metrics section which is present in source.

key_facts:
- Program for solution architects, ML engineers, instructors
- 8 tracks, 14 labs, 3 capstones
- Outcomes: prompts with safety/eval gates, hybrid RAG, eval release gates/telemetry, Agents SDK+AgentKit, multimodal/realtime, Codex, Apps SDK
- Flow: kickoff/setup, learning sprints, eval gates, capstone assembly
- Tracks include Prompt Engineering, Solution Blueprints, Agents & Tooling, AgentKit, Evals, Multimodality, Codex, Apps SDK
- Capstones: Field Intelligence Copilot; Autonomous Builder Control Tower
- Resources: repos, docs/courses, facilitation notes
summary:
The **OpenAI Partner Bootcamp Immersion** is an intensive program designed for **solution architects**, **ML engineers**, and **instructors** running OpenAI Immersion Days.

Key aspects of the program include:
- **Structure**: It features **eight immersive tracks**, **fourteen labs**, and **three high-touch capstones**, guiding participants from prompt engineering to multimodal agents with production-grade playbooks.
- **Program Outcomes**:
    - Shipping production-ready prompts with safety and evaluation gates.
    - Standing up hybrid **RAG** (Retrieval Augmented Generation) with orchestration and citations.
    - Running eval-driven release gates and telemetry loops.
    - Orchestrating **Agents SDK** + **AgentKit** workflows.
    - Building multimodal/realtime voice experiences, **Codex**-assisted flows, and **Apps SDK** chat applications.
- **Flow**: The program involves kickoff and setup, learning sprints with 30-minute primers and 60-minute labs, **eval gates** that drive pass/fail criteria, and capstone assembly.
- **Tracks**: Topics include **Prompt Engineering**, **Solution Blueprints**, **Agents & Tooling**, **AgentKit Systems**, **Evals & Benchmarking**, **Multimodality & Realtime**, **Codex & Agentic Dev UX**, and **Apps SDK Bootcamp**.
- **Capstones**: Participants blend learned tracks into final projects like "Field Intelligence Copilot" or "Autonomous Builder Control Tower".
- **Resources**: Bootcamp materials include source repositories, facilitator guides, **OpenAI Docs & Courses**, and immersion day notes.
notes: Accurate and comprehensive, but violates format rules: preamble, headings, and nested bullets; not bullet-only. Could be shorter.
